==============================================================================
Vendored dependencies
==============================================================================

The following submodules are vendored under `vendor/`. Each ships under
its own license; nothing under a copyleft license is linked into the
shipped Jacquard binary (see `docs/project-scope.md`).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vendor/eda-infra-rs/                           Apache-2.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Open-source Rust gate-level EDA infrastructure
(https://github.com/gzz2000/eda-infra-rs). Workspace-level license is
Apache-2.0 (vendor/eda-infra-rs/LICENSE).

Per-crate license declarations as of 2026-05-02:

  - clilog                 — Apache-2.0 (workspace)
  - netlistdb              — Apache-2.0 (workspace)
  - sverilogparse          — Apache-2.0 (workspace; see note below)
  - ucc                    — Apache-2.0 (workspace)
  - ulib                   — Apache-2.0 (workspace)
  - ulib_zeroable_derive   — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  - vcd-ng                 — MIT (Copyright 2015 Kevin Mehall)

NOTE: at the current submodule pin, `sverilogparse/Cargo.toml` still
declares `license = "AGPL-3.0-only"`. Per upstream maintainer
clarification (https://github.com/gzz2000/eda-infra-rs/issues/2#issuecomment-4363789319)
this is an unintentional declaration; the crate is governed by the
workspace LICENSE (Apache-2.0). Tracked as a follow-up to bump the
submodule pin once upstream pushes the fix; no Jacquard release ships
sverilogparse linked under AGPL terms.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vendor/sky130_fd_sc_hd/                        Apache-2.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SKY130 standard-cell library data files
(https://github.com/google/skywater-pdk-libs-sky130_fd_sc_hd).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vendor/opensta/                                GPL-3.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

OpenSTA static-timing analyzer (https://github.com/parallaxsw/OpenSTA).
GPL-3.0-licensed; **never linked, never bundled** into the shipped
Jacquard binary. Subprocess invocation only, per ADR 0001 and
ADR 0006 § Amendment. The vendored submodule is used by the
opensta-to-ir preprocessing tool and the timing-correctness CI corpus.

==============================================================================
Runtime dependencies discovered at build time
==============================================================================

Crate dependencies declared in Cargo.toml (and their transitive deps)
each carry their own licenses. Run `cargo license` or
`cargo about generate` against a tagged release for the full enumeration.
